 the even larger issues of spiritual ascension, predestination, and the human relationship to the Divine.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 4aAnthropology and Archaeology : Anthropology. 4aReligion and Spirituality : Islam. 4aReligion and Spirituality : Mysticism. 4aReligion and Spirituality : Sufism. 4aSociology : Sociology of Religion. 7aRELIGION / Islam / Sufi.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package 2024z978311149259940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143849690040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438496900423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438496900/original  a978-3-11-149259-9  SUNY Press eBook Package 2024b2024  aGBV-deGruyter-alles